# MAM DOWNLOADER IO - Backend API

```
cd backend
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
python app.py
```

Server runs on `http://localhost:5000`

## API Documentation

### POST /api/fetch
Fetch metadata from a URL

**Request:**
```json
{
  "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=..."
}
```

**Response:**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "url": "...",
  "platform": "youtube",
  "title": "...",
  "duration": 180,
  "thumbnail": "...",
  "formats": [...]
}
```

### POST /api/download
Start a download job

**Request:**
```json
{
  "url": "...",
  "format_id": "best",
  "quality": "1080p"
}
```

**Response:**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "job_id": "uuid",
  "status": "processing"
}
```

### GET /api/status/{job_id}
Get download status

**Response:**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "job_id": "uuid",
  "status": "downloading",
  "progress": 45.5,
  "speed": "2.5 MB/s",
  "eta": 120
}
```

### GET /api/history
Get download history

**Response:**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "history": [...]
}
```
